The Province average recovery remains 91%, representing a cumulative total of 98 668 people who have recovered from the disease. The number of total active cases stand at 6 603.

Frances Baard recorded the highest daily infections with 6 cases while the other three districts (JT Gaetsewe, Namakwa and ZF Mgcawu) had 2 cases each and no new cases were reported in the Pixley ka Seme district.
